taiepa
Homonym Number:
Word Class: noun
Sense Number:
Definition:in early use often spelt tie-up an old word for a fence, built usually of at-hand, bush materials. [Maori taiepa, taiapa]


Origin:
Register:
Register 2:
Domain: [none]
Region: [none]
See:
Pronunciation:
Notes:
Citations
Date:  4/6/1910
Source:  Evening Post
Author:
Vol / Page:  10
Edition:
Quote:  The entrance to the village marae, the assembly ground, in front of the carved meeting-house, "Tama-te-Kapu," is through a high taiepa or fence of manuka stakes, with carved posts, in imitation of the olden stockades, and a similar fence is erected in front of the carved Mission-hall "Te Ao-Marama" ("The World-of-Light"), where the Church of England Maori choir gives concerts and Maori dances.
